    "markdown": "---\ntitle: Nardia breidleri\nimage: \"../img/XXXXXX\"\ncategories:\n  - Marchantiophyta\n---\n\n\n<div class=\"info-panel\">\n <div class=\"info-top\">\n  <div class=\"taxon-scientific\"><span class=\"taxon-name\">Nardia breidleri</span> <span class=\"taxon-authority\">(Limpr.) Lindb.</span> <span class=\"taxon-family\">(Gymnomitriaceae)</span></div>\n  <div class=\"taxon-common\">Book Flapwort</div>\n </div>\n <div class=\"info-bottom\">\n  <div class=\"taxon-qnd\">XXXXXX</div>\n  <div class=\"taxon-abundance\">Rare</div>\n </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"imerss-content-frame\">\n <div class=\"imerss-image-header\">\n  <div class=\"imerss-image-holder imerss-column-left\" data-toggle=\"tooltip\" style=\"background-image: url(../img/XXXXXX)\" title=\"XXXXXX\">\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"imerss-image-holder imerss-column-right\" data-toggle=\"tooltip\" style=\"background-image: url(../img/XXXXXX)\" title=\"XXXXXX\">\n  </div>\n \n </div>\n <div class=\"imerss-content-lower\">\n  <div class=\"imerss-column-left\">\n  <div class=\"tab-microscope\" data-micromodal-trigger=\"modal-plate\">\n  <img src=\"../img/bryo guide microscope.png\"/>\n  </div>\n\n<h2>Distinguishing Features</h2>\n\nThe smallest species of Nardia in the region, N. breidleri has light-green to reddish-brown leafy shoots less than .5 mm wide that can be found around arctic and alpine regions growing on soil in areas of late snow melt. The lateral leaves are distantly-spaced ovate in shape with smooth margins and two slightly-unqual lobes that descend down 1/4 of the leaf's length, while the lateral leaf is simple, elongate and only visible near the apex of the stem along the underside. This is a &quot;dioicous&quot; species that under the microscope lacks obvious thickenings at the junctures between leaf cells, each cell housing one large, solitary oil body. \n\n<h2>Similar species</h2>\n\nXXXXXX\n\n<h2>Habitat</h2>\n\nMoist to wet humus, mineral soil, snowbed sites, and tundra in the subalpine and alpine zones\n\n<h2>Associated species</h2>\n\nXXXXXX\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"imerss-column-right\">\n\n<div class=\"imerss-image-holder imerss-column-right\" data-toggle=\"tooltip\" style=\"background-image: url(../img/XXXXX)\" title=\"XXXXX\">\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"imerss-map-holder\">\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-5a5703b43b2727b43965\" style=\"width:100%;height:464px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-5a5703b43b2727b43965\">{\"x\":{\"visdat\":{\"50f438913e78\":[\"function () \",\"plotlyVisDat\"]},\"cur_data\":\"50f438913e78\",\"attrs\":{\"50f438913e78\":{\"alpha_stroke\":1,\"sizes\":[10,100],\"spans\":[1,20],\"lat\":{},\"lon\":{},\"mode\":\"markers\",\"type\":\"scattermapbox\",\"color\":{},\"text\":{},\"size\":10,\"showlegend\":false,\"name\":{},\"marker\":{\"opacity\":0.59999999999999998},\"inherit\":true}},\"layout\":{\"margin\":{\"b\":0,\"l\":0,\"t\":0,\"r\":0},\"hovermode\":\"closest\",\"showlegend\":false,\"mapbox\":{\"style\":\"carto-positron\",\"zoom\":3.781124175131799,\"center\":{\"lon\":-130.30000000000001,\"lat\":54.600000000000001}},\"legend\":{\"x\":0.90000000000000002,\"y\":0.90000000000000002},\"autosize\":true},\"source\":\"A\",\"config\":{\"modeBarButtonsToAdd\":[\"hoverclosest\",\"hovercompare\"],\"showSendToCloud\":false},\"data\":[{\"lat\":[49.799999999999997,49.799999999999997],\"lon\":[-123,-123],\"mode\":\"markers\",\"type\":\"scattermapbox\",\"text\":[\"PRESERVED_SPECIMEN <br />Species: Nardia breidleri <br />Observed: August 18, 1962\",\"PRESERVED_SPECIMEN <br />Species: Nardia breidleri <br />Observed: August 10, 1962\"],\"showlegend\":false,\"name\":\"1962\",\"marker\":{\"color\":\"rgba(68,1,84,1)\",\"size\":[55,55],\"sizemode\":\"area\",\"opacity\":0.59999999999999998,\"line\":{\"color\":\"rgba(68,1,84,1)\"}},\"textfont\":{\"color\":\"rgba(68,1,84,1)\",\"size\":55},\"line\":{\"color\":\"rgba(68,1